cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with pre-trained language models and their ability to capture syntactic structures, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel method for extracting constituency trees, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of pre-trained LMs in correctly demarcating adverb phrases in sentences, which could potentially fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well, since it involves identifying and segmenting specific parts of an input.
